# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Adjustfile — Drift-tolerance contract for Axiom.jl
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>
#
# Cumulative-drift catchment: tolerance bands + corrective actions.
# Authority: advisory (Yard) — continue-with-warnings; auto_fix where deterministic.
# Run with: adjust check    Fix with: adjust fix
#
# NOTE (2026-06-13): rewritten for Axiom.jl. The estate-carried file was the
# rsr-template-repo Adjustfile (drift checks about "template placeholders").

@abstract:
Drift tolerances and corrective actions for Axiom.jl. Unlike MUST (hard
gate), ADJUST tracks cumulative drift against tolerance bands and proposes
corrective actions. Advisory — it warns and trends, it does not block.
@end

## Metadata Drift

### state-currency
- description: 6a2/STATE.a2ml last-updated should track real activity
- tolerance: last-updated within ~30 days of the most recent feature commit
- corrective: refresh .machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml (build snapshot + milestones)
- severity: advisory

### claude-md-path-accuracy
- description: CLAUDE.md must reference real artefact paths (no stale *.scm)
- tolerance: 0 references to non-existent .machine_readable paths
- corrective: reconcile CLAUDE.md "Machine-Readable Artefacts" with the actual 6a2/*.a2ml layout
- severity: advisory

## Governance Drift

### no-template-identity-leak
- description: contractiles must describe Axiom.jl, not rsr-template-repo
- tolerance: 0 contractiles claiming to be the canonical template
- corrective: substitute repo identity; rewrite template-role prose for Axiom.jl
- severity: advisory
- notes: the estate flat-contractile set shipped un-substituted (see Mustfile/Intentfile/Trustfile headers); upstream template fix is tracked separately

### contractile-completeness
- description: all six flat contractiles + Justfile present
- tolerance: Adjust/Bust/Dust/Intent/Must/Trust .a2ml + Justfile all exist
- corrective: add the missing contractile
- severity: advisory

## Code & Test Drift

### test-baseline
- description: Julia test suite should not silently regress
- tolerance: all testsets in test/runtests.jl pass (Tensor Types, Dense, Conv2d, Activations, Normalization, Pooling, Pipeline/Sequential, Optimizers, Coprocessor Backends, Loss Functions, Data Utilities, Serving APIs, Interop APIs, Verification, Ensure Macro, SMT Runner, SMT Cache)
- corrective: investigate dropped/ignored tests before merge
- severity: advisory

### no-template-identity-leak-band
- description: no contractile file claims repo identity is rsr-template-repo
- tolerance: 0 occurrences of identity-claim "rsr-template-repo" outside NOTE/check lines
- corrective: rewrite the offending contractile for this repo
- severity: advisory

## Hygiene Drift

### spdx-header-consistency
- description: all source files carry an SPDX-License-Identifier
- tolerance: 0 files missing SPDX headers
- corrective: add MPL-2.0 SPDX headers (the estate REUSE sweep covers the bulk)
- severity: advisory

### doc-currency
- description: README.adoc and ROADMAP.adoc should reflect current project state
- tolerance: no section describes a feature as "planned" if it has shipped
- corrective: update prose and status labels in affected docs
- severity: advisory
